Scan a repository for LLM artifacts

Usage:
  llm-lint scan [path] [flags]

Flags:
      --config string     config file path (relative to repo root) (default ".llmlint.yaml")
      --exclude strings   disable rule IDs (repeatable)
      --fail-on string    exit non-zero if any finding is at or above this severity (error|warning|info|none) (default "error")
      --format string     output format: human|json|sarif (default "human")
  -h, --help              help for scan
      --include strings   force-enable rule IDs (repeatable)
      --no-color          disable ANSI color
      --no-git            skip git history scan
      --no-progress       disable the live progress line on stderr
      --output string     output file or '-' for stdout (default "-")
      --since string      only scan commits since this git ref/sha
      --staged-only       scan files staged in the git index instead of the working tree (skips trailer/message rules)
  -v, --verbose           verbose output
